        <updateDate>2022-03-10T12:30:01Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>American Energy for Europe Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Energy (DOE) to evaluate the energy security of the United States and establish a program to reduce the reliance of allied European countries on natural gas, petroleum, and nuclear fuel produced in Russia. Under the program, DOE must provide resources, materials, equipment, financial assistance, and technical assistance to allies to reduce their reliance on Russian energy.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
